      <body>
         <bibl xml:id="work-1429" ana="#syriaca-saint">
            <title xml:id="name1429-1"
                   xml:lang="syr"
                   source="#bib1429-1"
                   syriaca-tags="#syriaca-headword">ܡܪܝܡ ܝܠܕܬ ܐܠܗܐ</title>
            <title xml:id="name1429-2" xml:lang="fr-x-bhsyre" source="#bib1429-1">Maryam yāldaṯ Alāhā</title>
            <title xml:id="name1429-3" xml:lang="fr" source="#bib1429-1">De Marie Mère de Dieu (mort)</title>
            <title xml:id="name1429-4"
                   xml:lang="en"
                   source="#bib1429-1"
                   syriaca-tags="#syriaca-headword">On on the Death of Mary Mother of God (Death)</title>
            <note xml:lang="syr" type="explicit" source="#bib1429-1">
               <quote>ܘܢܘܕܐ ܠܬܠܝܬܝܘܬܐ ܡܫܒܚܬܐ. ܐܒܐ ܘܒܪܐ ܘܪܘܚܐ ܩܕܝܫܐ. ܠܥܠܡ ܥܠܡܝܢ ܐܡܝܢ. ܘܪ̈ܚܡܝܟ ܡܪܢ ܘܚܢܢܟ ܘܛܝܒܘܬܟ. ܘܚܘܣܝܐ ܘܫܘܒܩܢܐ ܕܡܪܚܡܢܘܬܐ ܕܝܠܟ. ܢܐܬܘܢ ܘܢܫܬܦܥܘܢ ܥܠ ܡܝܚܠܐ... ܐܡܝܢ.</quote>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="fr" type="explicit" source="#bib1429-1">
               <quote>Et confessons la glorieuse Trinité, Père, Fils et Saint Esprit, pour les siècles des siècles. Amen.»  Que ta pitié, notre Seigneur, ta clémence, ta grâce, le pardon et la rémission de ta miséricorde viennent et se répandent sur le faible (scribe)… Amen.</quote>
            </note>
            <note type="editions">
               <bibl source="#bib1429-1">
                  <author>Wright, W.</author>
                  <title/>
                  <citedRange>Londres, 1865, p. 33-51 (syr.)</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </note>
            <note xml:lang="en" type="MSS" source="#bib1429-1">
               <bibl n="1">(Edited Above): ms Londres, British Library, Add. 12174, f. 449-452</bibl>
            </note>
